Supervised Feature Selection¶

Hypothesis Testing based feature selection using 𝑡t-Test¶

Two classes:

Class  𝝎1  with mean  𝜇1  variance  𝜎21Class  𝝎2  with mean  𝜇2  variance  𝜎22Class  ω1  with mean  μ1  variance  σ12Class  ω2  with mean  μ2  variance  σ22

Assumption: 𝜎21=𝜎22=𝜎2σ12=σ22=σ2

Hypothesis design for feature selection in classification problem:

𝐻1 (Difference between class means is non-zero): 𝐻0 (Difference between class means is zero): 𝜇1−𝜇2≠0𝜇1−𝜇2=0H1 (Difference between class means is non-zero): μ1−μ2≠0H0 (Difference between class means is zero): μ1−μ2=0

Feature with higher difference between class means has greater class separability, hence better feature.

Test Statistic¶

𝑞=(𝑥¯−𝑦¯)−(𝜇1−𝜇2)𝑠2𝑁‾‾‾√(1)(1)q=(x¯−y¯)−(μ1−μ2)s2N

where

𝑥¯=1𝑁∑𝑖=1𝑁𝑥𝑖,𝑥𝑖 are samples values of the feature in class 𝝎1𝑦¯=1𝑁∑𝑖=1𝑁𝑦𝑖,𝑦𝑖 are samples values of the feature in class 𝝎2𝑠2=12𝑁−2(∑𝑖=1𝑁(𝑥𝑖−𝑥¯)2+∑𝑖=1𝑁(𝑦𝑖−𝑦¯)2)class-wise sample variance.x¯=1N∑i=1Nxi,xi are samples values of the feature in class ω1y¯=1N∑i=1Nyi,yi are samples values of the feature in class ω2s2=12N−2(∑i=1N(xi−x¯)2+∑i=1N(yi−y¯)2)class-wise sample variance.

According to null-hypothesis 𝐻0H0, 𝜇1−𝜇2=0μ1−μ2=0

𝑞q follows 𝑡t-distributution with 2𝑁−22N−2 degrees of freedom.

For Feature 1:¶

In [2]:
f=X[,1]
fw1=f[1:N]
fw2=f[(N+1):(2*N)]
xbar=mean(fw1)
ybar=mean(fw2)
s=sqrt(sum((fw1-xbar)^2)+sum((fw2-ybar)^2)/(2*N-2))
q=(xbar-ybar)/(s*sqrt(2/N))
cat("\n xbar=",xbar," ybar=",ybar)
cat("\n\n Test statistic q= ",q)
cat("\n q follows t- distribution with ",2*N-2," degrees of freedom")

 xbar= 4.949148  ybar= 15.03573

 Test statistic q=  -7.19591
 q follows t- distribution with  398  degrees of freedom

Compute 𝑝p value

If p-value < 0.05: Feature has signficant difference between the class means

If p-value ≥≥ 0.05: Difference between class means along the feature is not significant

In [3]:
p.val=pt(q,2*N-2)
cat("\n p-value for hypothesis test on Feature 1= ",p.val)
alpha=0.05
if(p.val< alpha){
    cat("\n Feature is relevant")  
}else     
    cat("\n Feature  is not relevant, lacks class separability")

 p-value for hypothesis test on Feature 1=  1.5546e-12
 Feature is relevant

In [6]:
d=ncol(X)
q.val=rep(0,d)
for(i in 1:d)
{
    f=X[,i]
    fw1=f[1:N]
    fw2=f[(N+1):(2*N)]
    xbar=mean(fw1)
    ybar=mean(fw2)
    s=sqrt(sum((fw1-xbar)^2)+sum((fw2-ybar)^2)/(2*N-2))
    q=(xbar-ybar)/(s*sqrt(2/N))
    p.val=pt(q,2*N-2)
    cat("\n\n Test statistic q for Feature ",i," = ",q,"p-value=",p.val)
    q.val[i]=q
}
ord=sort(abs(q.val),decreasing=TRUE,index.return=TRUE)$ix
cat("\n\n Ordering of features based on t-Test=",ord)

 Test statistic q for Feature  1  =  -2.250143 p-value= 0.0124927

Feature selection using Fisher Discriminant Ratio¶

Multi-class case: ¶

Classes = 𝑀M¶

𝐹𝐷𝑅=∑𝑖=1𝑀∑𝑗≠𝑖𝑀(𝜇𝑖−𝜇𝑗)2𝜎2𝑖+𝜎2𝑗(2)(2)FDR=∑i=1M∑j≠iM(μi−μj)2σi2+σj2

In [8]:
nclass=length(unique(class))
FDR=rep(0,ncol(X))
for(d in 1:ncol(X))
{
    FDRd=0
    f=X[,d]
     for(i in 1:nclass)
     {
         for(j in 1:nclass)
         {
            if(i!=j)
            {
                fi=f[which(class==i)]
                fj=f[which(class==j)]
                FDRd=FDRd+((mean(fi)-mean(fj))^2)/(var(fi)+var(fj))
            }
            
         } 
     }
    cat("\n FDR for Feature ",d," = ",FDRd)
    FDR[d]=FDRd
}
ord=sort(abs(FDR),decreasing=TRUE,index.return=TRUE)$ix
cat("\n\n Ordering of features based on FDR: \n",paste0(colnames(X)[ord],collapse=", "))

𝑀M classes:   𝝎1, 𝝎2, ... , 𝝎𝑀  ω1, ω2, ... , ωM

Class-wise prior probability:

𝑃(𝝎𝑖)≃𝑁𝑖𝑁P(ωi)≃NiN
 𝑁𝑖 Ni number of samples in class 𝝎𝑖ωi out of a total of 𝑁N samples.

Class specific covariance matrix:

Σ𝑖=𝐸[(𝑥−𝜇𝑖)(𝑥−𝜇𝑖)𝑇]Σi=E[(x−μi)(x−μi)T]

Global mean vector:

𝜇0=∑𝑖=1𝑀𝑃(𝝎𝑖)𝜇𝑖μ0=∑i=1MP(ωi)μi

In [10]:
N=nrow(X)
nclass=length(unique(class))
mu0<-colMeans(X)
S<-list()
Mu<-list()
P<-list()
for(i in 1:nclass)
{
    wi=X[which(class==i),]
    Ni=nrow(wi)
    P[[i]]<-Ni/N
    Mu[[i]]<-colMeans(wi)
    S[[i]]<-cov(wi)
    cat("\n\n Class ",i,": ")
    cat("\n Prior P: ",P[[i]])
    cat("\n Mean Mu: ",Mu[[i]])
    cat("\n Covariance Matrix: \n")
    print(S[[i]])
}

Within-class scatter matrix ¶

𝑆𝑤=∑𝑖=1𝑀𝑃(𝝎𝑖)Σ𝑖(3)(3)Sw=∑i=1MP(ωi)Σi

Between-class scatter matrix ¶

𝑆𝑏=∑𝑖=1𝑀𝑃(𝝎𝑖)(𝜇𝑖−𝜇0)(𝜇𝑖−𝜇0)𝑇(4)(4)Sb=∑i=1MP(ωi)(μi−μ0)(μi−μ0)T

Mixture scatter matrix ¶

𝑆𝑚=𝐸[(𝑥−𝜇0)(𝑥−𝜇0)𝑇]=𝑆𝑤+𝑆𝑏(5)(5)Sm=E[(x−μ0)(x−μ0)T]=Sw+Sb
In [11]:
Sw=0
Sb=0
for(i in 1:nclass)
{
    mui0=Mu[[i]]-mu0
    Sw=Sw+ P[[i]]*S[[i]]
    Sb=Sb+ P[[i]]*outer(mui0,mui0)
}
Sm=Sw+Sb
cat("\n\n Within-class scatter matrix: \n")
print(Sw)
cat("\n\n Between-class scatter matrix: \n")
print(Sb)
cat("\n\n Mixture scatter matrix: \n")
print(Sm)

Class separability measures¶

𝐽1=𝑡𝑟𝑎𝑐𝑒{𝑆𝑚}𝑡𝑟𝑎𝑐𝑒{𝑆𝑤}(5)(5)J1=trace{Sm}trace{Sw}
𝐽2=|𝑆𝑚||𝑆𝑤|=|𝑆−1𝑤𝑆𝑚|(6)(6)J2=|Sm||Sw|=|Sw−1Sm|
𝐽3=𝑡𝑟𝑎𝑐𝑒{𝑆−1𝑤𝑆𝑚}(7)(7)J3=trace{Sw−1Sm}

|𝐴||A| denotes determinant of matrix 𝐴A.

In [12]:
J1=sum(diag(Sm))/sum(diag(Sw))
J2=det(solve(Sw)%*%Sm)
J3=sum(diag(solve(Sw)%*%Sm))
